  <body>
    <section name="Specify type layout">
     <span class="shortdesc">How to specify the elemental layout for a document type or compound type?</span>

   <script type="text/javascript">
    leftpx=250;
    bottompx=640;
   </script>
   <div class='group'>
    <div id='screenshot'><div>
     <img src="../../../../images/screenshots/cms_T07/inars/specify_type_layout.png" alt='Specify type layout'/>
    </div></div>
    <p>
      When you <a href='create_documenttype.html'>create a document type</a>
      and you have <a href='specify_type_details.html'>specified the type details</a>
      a dialog pops up where you can specify the elemental layout for the type.
      The dialog is the same for document types and compound types.
      You can choose from the available elemental layouts.
    </p>
   </div>

   <subsection name='Nested layout'>
    <p>
     When documents are edited in the document editor they are presented by a layout specified by
     their <a href='../concepts/documenttype.html'>document type</a>. The layout of the
     documents is composed by nesting the elemental layouts
     of the document type and its embedded compound types.
     See for a diagram the discussion of <a href='../concepts/compoundtype.html'>compound types</a>.
   </p>
   </subsection>

